Additional_Permit_Notes__c: ALL roof-mounted PV projects require an area variance and special use permit. This requires a 14-page application, and someone must go before the Zoning Board of Appeals, which meets on the 4th Thursday of the month. Usually the first meeting is just exploratory, and the decision is finalized at the second meeting, but it's possible we to get a decision in one meeting. Once the board approves, the building permit can be approved. The code enforcement officer recommends that the homeowner is the one to appear before the board. The code officer is willing to meet with the homeowner and help him/her through the process.
